{"title_page": "(G)I-dle discography", "text_new": "{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist           = (G)I-dle\n| Image            = (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4 (G)I-dle 10+Star Summer 04.png\n| Image size       = \t\n| Caption          = \n| Studio           = \t\n| EP               = 3\n| Live             = \t\n| Singles          = 5\n| Option name      = Other songs\n| Option           = 2\n| Soundtrack       = 2\n| Music videos     = 9\n| 1Option name     = Collaborations\n| 1Option          = 5\n}}\nSouth Korean girl group [[(G)I-dle]] have released three [[extended play]]s and seven [[Single (music)|digital single]]s. They have also participated in five collaboration songs, two soundtrack contributions and nine music videos.\n\nFormed by [[Cube Entertainment]] in 2018, (G)I-dle debuted in May 2, 2018 with EP ''[[I Am ((G)I-dle EP)|I Am]]'' with the song \"[[Latata]]\" as their first single. The group continued with the release of their first digital single titled \"[[Hann (Alone)]]\" on August 14, 2018 peaking at number 8 on the [[Gaon Music Chart]]. In 2019, they released their second mini album titled ''[[I Made]]'' on February 26, 2019 and followed by the released of their second digital single titled \"[[Uh-Oh ((G)I-dle song)|Uh-Oh]]\" on June 26. A month later, (G)I-dle began their venture into the Japanese music market with the release of ''[[Latata (EP)|Latata]]'' on July 31. The same year, two more singles\u2014\"[[I Made#Singles|Put It Straight\" (Nightmare Version)]] and \"[[Lion ((G)I-dle song)|Lion]]\"\u2014was released through their participation in [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s survival show ''[[Queendom (TV series)|Queendom]]''. \"Lion\" managed to gain commercial success and was nominated in [[Korean Music Awards]]. In 2020, (G)I-dle's third EP, ''[[I Trust]]'', and its lead single \"[[Oh My God ((G)I-dle song)|Oh My God]]\", were released on April 6. The EP becomes the group's best-selling album and the second-highest first day sales by a girl group at that time with total sales of 91,311 physical copies. It debuted atop both [[Gaon Album Chart]] and the Retail chart, moving more than 100,000 copies and scores their highest debut on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' World Albums chart.\n\n==Extended plays==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of extended plays, with selected chart positions and sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:6em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18em;\" | Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Sales\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Gaon Album Chart|KOR]]<br /><ref>Gaon Weekly Album Chart:\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=21&hitYear=2018&termGbn=week|title=I Am|date=May 20\u201326, 2018}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=09&hitYear=2019&termGbn=week|title=I Made|date=February 24 \u2013 March 2, 2018}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=15&hitYear=2020&termGbn=week|title=I Trust|date=April 5\u201311, 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Oricon Albums Chart|JPN]]<br /><ref>Oricon Albums Chart:\n* {{cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/ja/w/2019-08-12/|title=Latata|date=August 12, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Billboard Japan#Billboard Japan charts|JPN Hot]]<br /><ref>Billboard Japan Hot Albums:\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=hot_albums&year=2019&month=08&day=12|title=Latata|date=August 12, 2019}}</ref>\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"|[[Billboard charts|US World]]<br /><ref>''Billboard'' World Albums:\n* {{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts